<br>
Roughly speaking for pure damage spells at least, hate is proportional to nominal, as opposed to actual, damage.  If we are talking 2 kilo nuke, then it is going to generate about twice as much aggro as any of our current nukes.<br>
<br>
How long would you have to wait before casting another of these babies?  Especially given that the largest straight nuke (bar manaburn) given to wizzies is 2700 I think.<br>
<br>
Mages that do not have experience as enchanter or shaman alts, like myself, are going to be faced with something of learning curve here as regards aggro.  Practically the only spells we cast that generate noticeable aggro are nukes or other damage spells.  Malosini, damage shield, summoning, these are all low hate affairs.  It seems to me that aggro management has been a pretty darn straightforward affair for mages up to now.  Hell, I just right-click DS the shamans and enchanters 'cause I <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>knows</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> they gonna get aggro, and almost never me.  Well with charm and mezz I bet they start heading for us a lot more.<br>
<br>
I bet it will be not quite as simple as waiting a little while to toss the next nuke.<br>
<br>
From that point of view, a two kilo anti-summoned nuke would not involve as much change in mage aggro management, just more of the same, and one big honking nuke.<br>
<br>
Do mezz and charm generate so much aggro that we might have to wait a good long before nuking?  And if that is the case, then isn't aggro also a limitation on the enchanter nuke besides the long recast delay?<br>
<br>
I don't play an enchanter, I never have, so I don't know what its like to cast much non-damage aggro spells, and how to judge.  Maybe someone with a million alts or some n-boxer can enlighten me a little.<br>
<br>
